From 167ea040c9455ad47b991059e99560c4deef4dea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 09:18:36 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 19/22] fix(ui): treat multi-source path as configured once any
 source is covered

Previously a path was flagged as 'multiple sources without priority
configuration' if any of its sources was neither in per-path
priorities nor in the global source ranking. Ranking only the
preferred source left every competing source 'uncovered', so the
warning persisted after the user had already expressed a preference.

Invert the rule: if at least one source on the path is configured,
the user's intent is known and the warning is suppressed.
---
