Subject: [PATCH 22/22] fix(priorities): let configured source displace unknown
 incumbent
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Scott reported that a plugin source (venus.com.victronenergy.tank.20)
in the ranking was still losing to an unranked N2K Victron device
publishing the same tanks.fuel.0.* paths.

Root cause: getPrecedence returns HIGHESTPRECEDENCE (precedence 0)
for an unknown source that happens to be the current 'latest', while
any configured source gets its ranking position (precedence >= 0).
The latest-is-higher-precedence branch therefore required the
incoming configured source to outwait its own timeout of the
unknown incumbent's silence — but the N2K device never goes silent,
so the configured source can never win.

When the incoming source is configured and the incumbent is not,
accept immediately. A configured ranking always beats 'I have never
heard of this source before'.
